### QR Ticket Validation Testing

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api
@scannerToken = YOUR_SCANNER_OR_ADMIN_TOKEN

# Note: You can use an ADMIN token for these tests.

### 1. [ADMIN/SCANNER] Download Sync Data (Offline Prep)
# Replace :eventId with a real one (e.g., 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/validate/sync-data/1
Authorization: Bearer {{scannerToken}}

### 2. [ADMIN/SCANNER] Real-time Scan (Online)
# Use a qrPayload from a real ticket (see database or issue one)
POST {{baseUrl}}/validate/scan
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{scannerToken}}

{
    "qrPayload": "PASTE_QR_JWT_HERE",
    "gateId": "GATE-01",
    "deviceId": "SCANNER-MOB-01"
}

### 3. [ADMIN/SCANNER] Sync Offline Logs
POST {{baseUrl}}/validate/sync
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{scannerToken}}

{
    "logs": [
        {
            "qrPayload": "PASTE_QR_JWT_HERE",
            "gateId": "OFFLINE-GATE",
            "deviceId": "OFFLINE-DEV",
            "deviceTime": "2023-12-23T14:00:00Z"
        }
    ]
}
